---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const seo = {
  title: "Account Linking Redesign | Anna Kocaj",
  description:
    "Redesigning account linking at ASD Systems turned a process that could take up to 5 hours into one that takes a few minutes.",
  image: "/linked_accounts.png",
};
---

<Layout seo={seo}>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="mt-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6">
    <a
      href="/projects"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity text-sm mb-8"
    >
      ← Back to projects
    </a>

    <p class="text-sm opacity-50 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3 font-medium">
      Case Study · ASD Systems, 2024
    </p>
    <h1 class="font-bold text-3xl mb-4 leading-snug">
      Linked Accounts Redesign
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg opacity-70 mb-8 max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
      A process that could take up to 5 hours to set up one operator's access
      now takes a few minutes.
    </p>

    <!-- Overview grid -->
    <div
      class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-4 py-6 border-t border-b border-white/10 mb-10"
    >
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">My Role</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium">Sole Product Designer</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">Process</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium">Research, design and implementation</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">Tools</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium">Figma</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero image -->
    <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden m-6 bg-gray-800">
      <Image
        src="/linked_accounts.png"
        alt="Redesigned account linking interface"
        width={1200}
        height={675}
        class="w-full object-cover"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CHALLENGE -->
  <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-semibold text-xl mb-4">The Challenge</h2>
    <p class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Linking distributor accounts had existed as a complicated, monotonous
      manual process for years, largely unchanged as ASD Systems' client base
      grew. It was easy to make a mistake that and no one on the team could
      point to a real reason it had been built this way.
    </p>
    <p class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      The cost scaled badly with our biggest clients. For an existing
      distributor with 30 companies under them, granting a single new operator
      access across all of those companies could take <strong
        >up to 5 hours</strong
      > of manual linking. Clients were not able to manage this themselves, which
      meant every change became a support request.
    </p>
    <p class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed">
      The brief was clear: design a solution with backward compatibility for
      years of existing account data, that both our internal team and our
      clients could actually use.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- PROCESS -->
  <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-semibold text-xl mb-8">Process</h2>

    <div class="space-y-12">
      <!-- Step 1 -->
      <div>
        <p
          class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-2 font-medium"
        >
          01 — Define
        </p>
        <h3 class="font-medium text-base mb-3">
          Working within years of existing data
        </h3>
        <p class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          Before designing anything new, I needed to understand what the new
          solution had to preserve. The account-linking data went back years and
          touched every client, so backward compatibility wasn't optional. That
          constraint shaped the interface: whatever I designed had to represent
          existing links accurately from day one, not just new ones going
          forward.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 2 -->
      <div>
        <p
          class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-2 font-medium"
        >
          02 — Concept
        </p>
        <h3 class="font-medium text-base mb-3">
          One component, instead of a multi-step process
        </h3>
        <p class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
          I designed a "Linked Accounts" component directly inside the user
          creation and edit screen, replacing what had been a separate,
          error-prone process. Creating a link became a single, guided step:
        </p>
        <ul
          class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed text-sm list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 mb-4"
        >
          <li>Select the distributor to link the user with</li>
          <li>Select the role the user should have with that distributor</li>
          <li>Toggle whether the user can manage personal data</li>
          <li>Confirm and the link is added to the user's list</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 3 -->
      <div>
        <p
          class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-2 font-medium"
        >
          03 — Design & Validate
        </p>
        <h3 class="font-medium text-base mb-3">Making mistakes recoverable</h3>
        <p class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
          I designed a clear list of a user's current links, each removable with
          a single X and a confirmation popup. Before rollout, we validated the
          redesigned flow internally with our customer support team, who handled
          account-linking issues daily and could immediately tell where anything
          still felt unclear.
        </p>
        <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden m-6 bg-gray-800">
          <Image
            src="/linked_accounts.png"
            alt="Linked accounts list with removal confirmation popup"
            width={1200}
            height={675}
            class="w-full object-cover"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- OUTCOMES -->
    <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-xl mb-6">Outcomes</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5">
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold mb-1">5 hrs → minutes</p>
          <p class="text-sm opacity-60">
            to link a new operator across every company for a large distributor
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5">
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold mb-1">Self-service</p>
          <p class="text-sm opacity-60">
            clients could manage their own links for the first time, cutting
            support requests
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>

  <!-- NAVIGATION -->
  <section
    class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 mb-16 flex justify-center items-center border-t border-white/10 pt-8"
  >
    <a
      href="/projects"
      class="opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity text-sm"
    >
      ← All projects
    </a>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  strong {
    color: white;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  em {
    color: inherit;
  }
</style>
